    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The text in the parting <sic>adress</sic><lb/> of <persName>Rev.
                    Wise</persName> was from <add>יהושע א פסוק ח'</add><lb/>
                <add>לא ימוש ספר התורה הזה מפיך והגית בו יום ולילה למען תשכיל</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The main point of his text consisted<lb/> in the word
                    <add>לֹא-יָמוּשׁ סֵפֶר הַתּוֹרָה הַזֶּה מִפִּיךָ, וְהָגִיתָ בּוֹ יוֹמָם
                    וָלַיְלָה, לְמַעַן תִּשְׁמֹר לַעֲשׂוֹת, כְּכָל-הַכָּתוּב בּוֹ</add> that then
                must<lb/> be wiser and get younger and wiser<lb/> senses, like
                    <persName>Josua</persName> had <sic>whenn</sic> He<lb/> was appointed in the
                place of <persName>Moses</persName><lb/> He then <persName>Wise</persName> alluded
                with his<lb/> text, the following maxim</p>
            <p>Thou must <add>כִּי-אָז תַּצְלִיחַ אֶת-דְּרָכֶךָ, וְאָז תַּשְׂכִּיל.</add><lb/> Keep
                    <add>למען תשכיל</add> solemn; but in the<lb/> way of having different
                ceremonies<lb/> to <del>shorten</del> have the prayers <add>לא ימוש ספר התורה הזה
                    מפיך</add> accor˶<lb/>ding <persName>Rev Wise's </persName>fancy shortened<lb/>
                to have an Organ <add>יום כפיר כיפור</add><lb/> You must be wiser in that
                respect<lb/> principally here in this blessed<lb/> free country <add>תפילות</add>
                more<lb/> and in different way than you <sic>was</sic><lb/> in olden times</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>We have got the right here<lb/> in this country to praise<lb/> and pray to our God
                with<lb/> out fear of being disturbed<lb/> or prosecuted so we have also<lb/> a
                temple <add>למען תשכיל</add> and can<lb/> have an organ like the levitten<lb/> had
                instruments in the<lb/> temple of <persName>Solomon</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">His parting <sic>adress</sic> was<lb/> the allusion to the
                following<lb/> 3 points first <add>ארץ זבת חלב ודבש</add><lb/> And thou shall teach
                your<lb/> children first diligently the<lb/>
                <add>בית המקדש</add> Second <add>ושננתם לבניך</add> You must<lb/> yourself speak
                constant of<lb/> the <add>תורה</add> and study in it <sic>whenn</sic><lb/> thou
                sittest in thy house etc and<lb/> last <add>ודברת בם</add><lb/> Have peace among
                yourself <add>?</add></p>
        </body>
